bug.short_desc: CSS problems when searching many projects at once

long_desc.thetext:
From internal bug report:
--- Do this search: - go to http://<opengrok-instance>:8080/source/index.jsp - 'select all' gates - run Filepath search for valid package name, for instance
You get to with a different links. If you click on the link, the page is empty (for me).
It's behaving strange, sometimes if I copy the URL to a new browser tab, it displays.
It seems that the huge search somehow tires opengrok, who is then unwilling to serve any content :) ---
It seems like CSS corruption of sorts.
Sometimes I even get empty page as a result of the search.

Created attachment 4552 screenshot demonstrating the problem
this is how it looks like when opengrok displays the result of all-project search.

Hmmm, works for me, but it may depend on the repos (I just got 7099 results).
I wonder whether you would get the same behavior with a recent opengrok-snapshot...
For now I would blame the browser ;-) If you don't think so, the html source of what you browser got would be interesting...
BTW: What version do you use.
Lubos/Knut/Trond: Is it possible to add the version fields in bugzilla, so that people can submit this info, when reporting a bug?

(In reply to comment #3) > Hmmm, works for me, but it may depend on the repos (I just got 7099 results). > > I wonder whether you would get the same behavior with a recent > opengrok-snapshot...
Can't test unfortunately, since our deployment is sort of operationally critical.
> For now I would blame the browser ;-) If you don't think so, the html source of > what you browser got would be interesting...
